args: Hmm, there's a flyer on the ground.\nPerhaps someone brought it here\nfrom a neighboring village.
Ooo, it's an ad for a new play!\n＂Struggles of a New Bride:\nThe In-Laws from Hell.＂
Do humans find this kind of sordid familial\ndrama entertaining?
This Mym's imagination, people and places,\nnothing is real, yadda yadda yadda.
Mym! I just found a speck of dust when I\nlooked beneath the couch. Your cleaning\nskills are simply atrocious!
Apologies won't make this pigsty clean!\nHonestly, you are a useless wife.
Is my meal done yet, girl?!
Lies! You're tryin' to starve me and take\nthe inheritance! You're a wife from hell!
Sister-in-law, I'm borrowing some of your\nsecret savings. Once I win big at the track,\nI'll pay you back double!
You said that last time, and I STILL\nhaven't seen any of that money!
You're old enough to stop floating\naimlessly through life and get a job.
Quiet, you! The key is to work smarter,\nNOT harder! Everyone knows that!
This is s-so hard... But as long\nas my darling is with me...
But today's our wedding anniversary!\nYou promised that we could celebrate\nit together this year!
Tough cookies, cookie! He's going to\nthe hot springs with a REAL woman!
You... You're his secretary! Nooooo!\nYou're having an AFFAIR!
Hey, if you hadn't let all your womanly\ncharms go, he wouldn't have needed\nto come to me. ZING!
Come, lover. Let us be off.
Take my hand and we will go, dear!
Crikey! This 'ere's the 'ouse what where\n{player_name} lives.
Ah, you must be the wife. We're here to\ncollect on your husband's MANY debts.
Yeah, 'e owes big to the boss man, see?\nAnd we's come make sure the bill's paid!
I have the promissory note right here.\nFeel free to look it over.
...I've never SEEN so many zeros!\nHe'll never be able to pay!
Well then, I suppose we'll have to\nsecure the money in another fashion.
Lotta rich folks would pay dear to get\ntheir mitts on a real-life dragon.
We can do whatever we likes, so we can!
You said so yourself, there's no other way\nhe'd be able to pay up.
Darling! You...you came back for me?

I'm so sorry, my love! I realized the error
of my ways and told that awful secretary 
of mine to take her poor filing skills and
terrible penmanship elsewhere!
YOU are the only one I need!
It's okay, darling. You don't have to\napologize anymore...
We're all going to see a new play.\nWould you care to join us?
Mym? What are you... Mym, wait!\nCalm down! AAAIIIEEEEEE!
